review_blob: Dark amber / brown color. Smells prunes, buckwheat honey, malt and bakery yeast. Medium body with malty focus and quite solid alcohol mouthwash. Hint of caramel in the aftertaste.

Pitch black with small head. Smells single malt wisky. Full body, lits of alcohol. Tastes wisky, wine and some roast bread. Not bitter. Good balance with the exception of a sour spike on the aftertaste.
beer_name: The Kernel Imperial Brown Stout (Marc de Bourgogne)

review_blob: Medium head, dark amber and murky. Smells quince jam. Full malty body. Tastes fruit, quince, and a bit of alcohol. There is a slight sourness in the aftertaste though. Very good

Medium thick head. Golden, slightly hazy and bright. Lots of carb. Smells canned peach and tropical fruit. Slightly artificial aroma. Medium body, same canned fruit in the taste. Balance on the sweet side. Refreshing and drinkable.
Amber, hazy, small head, some sediment on the bottom. Intense hops in the aroma: tropical fruits, catty scent (nelson?). Medium body, perfectly balanced with a sharp bitter finish.
Big head. Dark golden color. Tropical fruits in the aroma, hops. Sweet body with a proper bitter finish. Good
Dark brown, small thin head. Smells smoky bacon. Taste is meaty and smoky with gentle bitterness in the medium body which makes the beer quite refreshing and easy drinking. Nice
Straw color. Small head. Smells sewers and marsh. Light body, crisp and refreshing. Tastes spices, perfume and lemongrass. Light hoppy bitterness in the end.
Pale golden color. No head. Smells barley, oatmeal and grain. Grain and honey in the taste. No hops at all. Not crisp and not refreshing
Dark amber, close to red. no head. Smells nothing. Bitter finish. Watery body. Ordinary, but drinkable and with no defects.
Very small head. Black. Smells roast and chocolate. Thick body. Tastes chocolate and some roasted malts on the end. Long sweet finish is a bit artificial though.

Amber color. Small creamy head. Lots of carb and a bit hazy. Fruity citrusy aroma. Unexpectedly sweet and malty body with strong bitterness hovering it. Tastes empty though. Drinkable but not bursting with flavor at all
Small but thick coffee head. Dark brown (almost black). Smells cheap instant coffee, fresh coffee beans, green peas and celery. Taste vegetables with a hont of roast. Body is medium.
Small head. Dark brown. Light aroma of malt, wine and roast bread. Light body, quite watery. tastes roast with an unbalanced bitterness in the end. Drinkable.
Big head, clear golden color. Smells zest, malt, belgian yeast. Medium body with some malt and perfume. Slightly watery and overcarbonated. Theres also an unpleasant acid spike in the finish.

Straw color, medium but thick and creamy head. Some carb. Glass and beer are overchilled :( But smells malt and wheat. Medium body with more malts and wheat in the taste. Some witbier sout spike tickling the throat. Good, but a bit empty.
Thin head. Hazy golden. Smells tropical fruit, zest. Body is mild and medium. Very light bitterness in the finish. Very good and Id say session beer (despite high abv)
beer_name: The Kernel India Pale Ale Simcoe Sticklebract

review_blob: On tap in Brewdog shoreditch. Deep amber (perfect) color. Small head. Smells wine, alcohol and/but chlorine/medicine/hospital/sterile flavor. Taste is very smoky with the same sterile hint and aftertaste.
Almost no head. Coffee foam. Black with a hint of brown color. Smell alcohol, roast, wine and sour (close to vinegar). Lots of alcohol and some weird sour spike in the taste. Roast finish.

Thick head. Dark brown, almost black color. Smells wine and bread that is about to be toasted. The mildest non-nitro beer Ive ever tried. Sweet bread, roast that is there for you in the aftertaste as well. Light bitterness in the finish. Good.

Clear golden. Small head. Floral aroma witg some ripe fruit on the backend. Spices in the taste along with the raisins and citrus zest. Theres something else I cant figure out, which makes it totally different from normal ipa. But quite decent drink.
Hazy, dirty amber color. Small head. Smells dry/ripe fruit. Tastes smoky prunes with focus on the bitter side.
Clear golden color. Small head. Smells spices, honey, wheat. Tastes candy. More spices in the aftertaste (pepper). A little bit heavy for saison.

Murky. Not transparent at all. Raspberry-red color. Medium head. Smells berries, raspberry and distant hops. Taste is a bit sour and empty. This was very over cooled so not much to add. More berries in the taste upon warming up and sourish finish

Amber color. Huge creamy thick head. Some carbonation. Smells grass, herbs, hops. Very floral. Medium a bit oily body with bitter focus and nice long bitter finish. Tastes usual IPA. Good, but not exceptional

Dark brown. Not transparent with huge creamy head. Smells malt, wine, dark fruit, alcohol and some nuts. Thick body, no carb. Sweet, fruity and malty. No alcohol in the taste. There's some alcohol in the finish though.

Golden, not quite transparent. Head doesn't stay long. Very intense aroma. Smells candy (sorachi?), some perfume, tropical fruit and cucumber. Hoppy, fruity flavor in a medium body with both bitter and candy / cucumber aftertaste. Refreshing

Deep brown color with small head. Smell malt, ripe fruit and caramel. Similar to esb or london pride. Medium body with some carb and bitter focus in the finish. Flavor itself is malty and fruity. Refreshing
Golden color, big head that quickly fades away. Some carb. Smells grass and hops. Taste is crisp, refreshing with light bitter focus. Some honey notes in the finish. Good summer beer.
Straw color. No head and a little carb. Smells honey, grass, flowers and sweet white wine. More wine in the taste along with the same flowers and grass. Medium body with nice long bitter finish.

Light gold colour. Head quickly goes away. Smells yeast, flowers, mandarine/orange. Watery body with nice yeast finish. Balance on the sweet side. A bit lacks in palate, but overall good and quite drinkable.
On draft from a mug. Golden, hazy with medium head. Smells cut grass, herbs and some yeast. Unclear flavor with no bitterness or sweetness and thus quite empty. Lager finish.

Thick high head. Bronze color. Very murky. Smells toffee, quince, ripe fruit. Body holds a lot of carb and is quite empty with that sour finish of hefe weisbier. There are same ripe fruit in the taste

Transparent dark gold liquid with thin head. Smells hops, grass and grapefruit zest with a bit of a metal scent. Medium watery body, some honey in the taste and nice medium-bitter aftertaste (gentle and not harsh). A bit more carb than necessary
Head quickly fades away. Brownish black color. Smells wine, plums, quince jam. Tastes roast bread, wine, ripe fruit. Balance on sweet side. Carbonation tickles the mouth. Very good.
Amber color. Lots of carb. Thick huge head. Smells hops and some honey. Nice bitterness on the tongue, good finish. But does not taste IPA. It's a hopped pils rather than india pale

beer_brewer_name: Bernard Family Brewery / Rodinn pivovar Bernard
review_blob: Dark brown with creamy head (not very thick but stays quite long). Smells malt, wine and ripe fruit. Tastes coffee, roasted bread crumbs. Medium to thick body with the ficus on sweeter side. Aftertaste has some kind of unpleasant sour spike. But overall quite good and drinkable.
beer_name: Bernard ern Lek 12 / Bernard Dark Lager

review_blob: Light coffee aroma, some roast (not intense). Thin brown head. Looks black. Medium watery body with good bitter finish. Tastes roast bread. Quite dry and easy to drink
Pitch black, medium coffee color head. Smells fruit (cherry?, plums). Rich body. Robusta, coffee and some acid aftertaste. Not really exceptional, but proper imp stout.
Light golden color. Head quickly goes away. Smells malt, honey and some hops. Has that faulty acid / metallic aftertaste in the end. Otherwise - drinkable.

Brown and hazy. Long lasting carbonation. No head. Smells wine, sour / Brett with a bit of vinegar. Empty body with sour / acid finish. Some sweet malty and alcohol notes are present throughout taste and aftertaste
beer_name: Bush de Nuits (Scaldis Prestige de Nuits)

review_blob: Rich bronze colour. Murky. Thin head. Smells sour with vinegar, young wine. Very nice sweet taste. No alcohol for 13 abv. Beer tickles the tongue with almost no carbonation. Some acidity in sourness in aftertaste, which is less aggressive than the one in aroma.
No head, pitch black. Roasted bread crumbs, some malt and a tint of beans. Black bread in the taste. Lots of alcohol and very roasted aftertaste. Easy and pleasant to drink though.
beer_name: The Kernel Imperial Brown Stout London 1856

review_blob: No head. Brownish black colour. Grassy, fruity, catty nelson flavour. Tiny hint of chocolate in the taste, some unbalanced bitterness, nevertheless very mild. Solid black ipa with long bitter finish
beer_name: The Kernel India Pale Ale Black

review_blob: Dark amber clear color. Smells honey, pilsner hops and some malt. Metal but malty taste in a thin body. Very usual macro style drink
No head. Brown color. Very hazy. Light quince aroma. Sweet candy and perfume in the taste. Caramel and creme brle. A bit rough and bitter finish with some biscuits in the end. Very good balance

Dark amber color, no head. Murky. Aroma of quince jam. You can smell how thick is the body even. Mild alcohol in the taste. Jam disappears, Some ripe fruits and grapes. Finish is a bit rough, goes away quickly, but still leaves a pleasant aftertaste.

Gold color. Small carb. Quite clear for unfiltered beer. Smells caramel, malt a little bit of alcohol. Honey in the taste, alcohol and caramel disappears quite quickly. Malty and watery aftertaste with a tint of bitterness. Good for a pills.

Thin lager head. Clear Dark amber color. Smells caramel, malts and alcohol. Thin body with candy, caramel and again alcohol. Seems like a beer that is stronger than it actually is. Alcohol in the aftertaste.
beer_name: Suntory The Premium Malts Hojun Ale

review_blob: Smells sour and yeast and young wine. Hazy and murky for a pills. Light pale color. Tastes wine and vinegar with some sourness. No malt and no hops. Watery aftertaste. Ok for 1 time, but not a pills
